    "# NB02 — Testing with pytest\n",
    "\n",
    "**Module 16 — Research Software Engineering**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "A function that has never been tested is a function that has never been proven to work. In computational biology, an untested function is worse than no function at all — it produces wrong answers silently. A wrong GC-content calculation, a reversed complement that isn't actually reversed, a p-value corrected with the wrong method: these are the bugs that make papers get retracted. Testing is not optional.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Intuition\n",
    "\n",
    "A test is three things: **Arrange** (set up inputs), **Act** (call the function), **Assert** (check the output matches expectations). When the assertion fails, pytest tells you exactly what went wrong, with the actual and expected values side by side. You run your entire test suite in seconds and know immediately if any change broke any function.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Biological Background\n",
    "\n",
    "The two functions we test here are:\n",
    "- `reverse_complement`: if the template strand is 5'-ATCG-3', the complement is 3'-TAGC-5', which read 5'-to-3' is 5'-CGAT-3'. This is foundational to PCR primer design, restriction enzyme recognition, and sequence alignment.\n",
    "- `gc_content`: GC base pairs are held by three hydrogen bonds versus two for AT, making GC-rich regions more thermally stable. GC content correlates with gene density, codon usage bias, and PCR efficiency.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Mathematical / Conceptual Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "- `reverse_complement(seq)`: complement each base (A↔T, C↔G), then reverse the string.\n",
    "- `gc_content(seq)`: GC% = (count(G) + count(C)) / len(seq). Edge case: empty sequence → return 0.0 (or raise ValueError — decide and document).\n",
    "\n",
    "The key concepts in pytest:\n",
    "- **`@pytest.mark.parametrize`**: run the same test with multiple input/output pairs — avoids copy-paste test duplication.\n",
    "- **Fixture**: a function decorated with `@pytest.fixture` that provides shared setup to multiple tests. Fixtures are dependency-injected by name.\n",
    "- **`pytest.raises`**: assert that a specific exception is raised for invalid input.\n",
    "- **`conftest.py`**: module-level fixtures that pytest discovers automatically.\n",
    "- **Coverage**: fraction of source lines executed during testing — `pytest --cov=compbio_utils`.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Implement the two functions under test\n",
    "def reverse_complement(seq: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return the reverse complement of a DNA sequence.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    seq : str\n",
    "        DNA sequence using IUPAC characters (A, T, C, G only for this version).\n",
    "        Case-insensitive; output is uppercase.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    str\n",
    "        Reverse complement of ``seq``, uppercase.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Raises\n",
    "    ------\n",
    "    ValueError\n",
    "        If ``seq`` contains characters outside {A, T, C, G} (case-insensitive).\n",
    "\n",
    "    Examples\n",
    "    --------\n",
    "    >>> reverse_complement('ATCG')\n",
    "    'CGAT'\n",
    "    >>> reverse_complement('AAAA')\n",
    "    'TTTT'\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    seq = seq.upper()\n",
    "    valid = set('ATCG')\n",
    "    invalid = set(seq) - valid\n",
    "    if invalid:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f'Invalid nucleotide(s): {\", \".join(sorted(invalid))}')\n",
    "    complement = str.maketrans('ATCG', 'TAGC')\n",
    "    return seq.translate(complement)[::-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def gc_content(seq: str) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Compute the GC content of a DNA sequence.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    seq : str\n",
    "        DNA sequence. Case-insensitive.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    float\n",
    "        Fraction of G and C bases in [0.0, 1.0]. Returns 0.0 for empty sequences.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Raises\n",
    "    ------\n",
    "    ValueError\n",
    "        If ``seq`` contains non-ATCG characters.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Examples\n",
    "    --------\n",
    "    >>> gc_content('ATCG')\n",
    "    0.5\n",
    "    >>> gc_content('AAAA')\n",
    "    0.0\n",
    "    >>> gc_content('')\n",
    "    0.0\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not seq:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    seq = seq.upper()\n",
    "    valid = set('ATCG')\n",
    "    invalid = set(seq) - valid\n",
    "    if invalid:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f'Invalid nucleotide(s): {\", \".join(sorted(invalid))}')\n",
    "    return (seq.count('G') + seq.count('C')) / len(seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Quick sanity checks\n",
    "assert reverse_complement('ATCG') == 'CGAT'\n",
    "assert reverse_complement('AAAA') == 'TTTT'\n",
    "assert gc_content('ATCG') == 0.5\n",
    "assert gc_content('') == 0.0\n",
    "print('Sanity checks passed.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Writing Tests: Arrange–Act–Assert\n",
    "\n",
    "We write tests in pure Python first (no pytest runner in the notebook), then explain how pytest would run them."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pytest\n",
    "import textwrap\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demonstrate pytest.mark.parametrize conceptually\n",
    "# These are the test cases we'd put in test_sequence.py\n",
    "\n",
    "REVCOMP_CASES = [\n",
    "    # (input, expected_output, test_id)\n",
    "    ('ATCG',       'CGAT',       'basic_four_bases'),\n",
    "    ('AAAA',       'TTTT',       'all_adenine'),\n",
    "    ('CCCC',       'GGGG',       'all_cytosine'),\n",
    "    ('GCGC',       'GCGC',       'palindrome'),\n",
    "    ('A',          'T',          'single_base_A'),\n",
    "    ('T',          'A',          'single_base_T'),\n",
    "    ('G',          'C',          'single_base_G'),\n",
    "    ('C',          'G',          'single_base_C'),\n",
    "    ('atcg',       'CGAT',       'lowercase_input'),\n",
    "    ('ATCGATCG',   'CGATCGAT',   'eight_bases'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "GC_CASES = [\n",
    "    ('ATCG',   0.5,  'equal_mix'),\n",
    "    ('AAAA',   0.0,  'all_A'),\n",
    "    ('CCCC',   1.0,  'all_C'),\n",
    "    ('GGGG',   1.0,  'all_G'),\n",
    "    ('TTTT',   0.0,  'all_T'),\n",
    "    ('',       0.0,  'empty_string'),\n",
    "    ('ATCGATCG', 0.5, 'eight_bases_half'),\n",
    "    ('GCGCGCGC', 1.0, 'all_gc'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run them all\n",
    "passed = 0\n",
    "failed = 0\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for seq, expected, test_id in REVCOMP_CASES:\n",
    "    actual = reverse_complement(seq)\n",
    "    ok = actual == expected\n",
    "    results.append(('revcomp', test_id, seq, expected, actual, ok))\n",
    "    passed += ok\n",
    "    failed += not ok\n",
    "\n",
    "for seq, expected, test_id in GC_CASES:\n",
    "    actual = gc_content(seq)\n",
    "    ok = abs(actual - expected) < 1e-10\n",
    "    results.append(('gc_content', test_id, seq, expected, actual, ok))\n",
    "    passed += ok\n",
    "    failed += not ok\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Results: {passed} passed, {failed} failed')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test invalid input with pytest.raises\n",
    "import traceback\n",
    "\n",
    "invalid_inputs = [\n",
    "    ('ATCGN', 'N is not a standard IUPAC strict base'),\n",
    "    ('ATCG1', 'digit is not a nucleotide'),\n",
    "    ('ATCG ', 'space is not a nucleotide'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Testing ValueError on invalid input:')\n",
    "for seq, reason in invalid_inputs:\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        reverse_complement(seq)\n",
    "        print(f'  FAIL: {repr(seq)} did not raise ValueError ({reason})')\n",
    "    except ValueError as e:\n",
    "        print(f'  PASS: {repr(seq)} raised ValueError: {e}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Show what the actual pytest test file looks like\n",
    "test_file_content = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n",
    "    # tests/test_sequence.py\n",
    "    import pytest\n",
    "    from compbio_utils.sequence import reverse_complement, gc_content\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    @pytest.mark.parametrize('seq,expected', [\n",
    "        ('ATCG',     'CGAT'),\n",
    "        ('AAAA',     'TTTT'),\n",
    "        ('CCCC',     'GGGG'),\n",
    "        ('GCGC',     'GCGC'),\n",
    "        ('A',        'T'),\n",
    "        ('T',        'A'),\n",
    "        ('G',        'C'),\n",
    "        ('C',        'G'),\n",
    "        ('atcg',     'CGAT'),\n",
    "        ('ATCGATCG', 'CGATCGAT'),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    def test_reverse_complement_valid(seq, expected):\n",
    "        assert reverse_complement(seq) == expected\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    @pytest.mark.parametrize('seq', ['ATCGN', 'ATCG1', 'ATCG '])\n",
    "    def test_reverse_complement_invalid_raises(seq):\n",
    "        with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n",
    "            reverse_complement(seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    @pytest.mark.parametrize('seq,expected', [\n",
    "        ('ATCG',     0.5),\n",
    "        ('AAAA',     0.0),\n",
    "        ('CCCC',     1.0),\n",
    "        ('GGGG',     1.0),\n",
    "        ('TTTT',     0.0),\n",
    "        ('',         0.0),\n",
    "        ('ATCGATCG', 0.5),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    def test_gc_content_valid(seq, expected):\n",
    "        assert gc_content(seq) == pytest.approx(expected)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    # conftest.py fixture example:\n",
    "    # @pytest.fixture\n",
    "    # def sample_dna():\n",
    "    #     return 'ATCGATCGATCG'\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    # def test_gc_content_fixture(sample_dna):\n",
    "    #     assert gc_content(sample_dna) == pytest.approx(0.5)\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(test_file_content)"
   ]
  },
